00:00:31.749 --> 00:00:33.410
Human hair is mostly made of keratin.

00:00:33.410 --> 00:00:35.770
Nature loves this fibrous stuff.

00:00:35.770 --> 00:00:41.801
It cover antlers, makes up claws, and protects
shells and hydes -- but in humans we use it

00:00:41.801 --> 00:00:45.200
for making hair and the outermost layer of
skin.

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:50.170
The BBC reported in 2010 that 100 grams of
blonde, European human hair was worth as much

00:00:50.170 --> 00:00:53.410
as 1,000 pounds sterling!

00:00:53.410 --> 00:00:59.770
According to the Hair Price calculator at
HairSellOn.com: 10 inches of regular brown

00:00:59.770 --> 00:01:02.950
