00:01:02.950 --> 00:01:06.470
We use this natural, renewable resource for
a bunch of things already.

00:01:06.470 --> 00:01:09.619
It's used for food, construction, vanity,
fashion and art.

00:01:09.619 --> 00:01:11.450
Yes, I said food.

00:01:11.450 --> 00:01:17.229
Other than keratin, human hair contains L-cysteine
-- a flavor enhancing amino acid.

00:01:17.229 --> 00:01:21.840
You might see it on food labels as "dough
conditioner," "reaction flavor" or "E920"

00:01:21.840 --> 00:01:24.100
in the U.K..

00:01:24.100 --> 00:01:28.670
You could be eating hair in pizza dough and
not even know it!

00:01:28.670 --> 00:01:34.149
Darker, straighter hair was easier to extract
the L-cysteine, so most companies used hair

00:01:34.149 --> 00:01:40.450
from China and India -- but once word got
out and people got grossed out, now it's taken

00:01:40.450 --> 00:01:44.679
from duck feathers or altogether synthetic.

00:01:44.679 --> 00:01:48.601
The synthetic version is halal, kosher, and
vegan!

00:01:48.601 --> 00:01:53.320
A Chinese company used the amino acids in
human hair to make soy sauce 'til they got

00:01:53.320 --> 00:01:54.320
